1) Write your first Shell Script to print Hello world

Open a file Hello.sh with the contents below
echo "Hello World";

- In the shell type the command sh Hello.sh


2) Write a shell script with a variable

Open a file Hello.sh with the contents below
echo "Hello World";
echo "Hello $USER";

- Run the shell script with sh Hello.sh


3) Write a shell script with variables

Open a file Hello.sh with the contents below
echo "Hello World";
echo "Hello $USER";
echo "My shell is $SHELL";

- Run the shell script with sh Hello.sh

4) Write a shell script to display the processes
echo " Running Process List";
ps;
